  "local_port": 40096,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I tell Google to deindex my all pages site?",
  "response": "To tell Google to deindex all pages of your site, you can use the Google Search Console and modify your site's robots.txt file. Here are the steps to follow:\n\n### Using Google Search Console:\n\n1. **Verify Ownership of Your Site**: Make sure you have verified ownership of your site in Google Search Console.\n2. **Remove URLs**:\n   - Go to the Google Search Console.\n   - Select the property (website) you want to deindex.\n   - In the left-hand menu, click on \"Removals.\"\n   - Click on the \u201cNew Request\u201d button.\n   - Choose the \"Temporarily remove URL\" option.\n   - Enter the URLs you want to remove. If you want to remove all pages, you need to enter each URL individually or use a URL pattern that covers all pages.\n   - Submit your request.\n\n### Using robots.txt File:\n\n1. **Create or Edit robots.txt**:\n   - Access your website\u2019s root directory.\n   - Create a file named `robots.txt` if it doesn\u2019t already exist.\n   - Add the following directives to the file:\n\n     ```\n     User-agent: *\n     Disallow: /\n     ```\n\n   This tells all search engines not to crawl any pages on your site.\n\n2. **Upload the robots.txt File**:\n   - Save and upload the `robots.txt` file to your website\u2019s root directory.\n\n### Using Meta Tags (Optional):\n\n1. **Add Noindex Meta Tag**:\n   - If you want to ensure that specific pages are not indexed, you can add the following meta tag to the `<head>` section of your HTML for each page you want to deindex:\n\n     ```html\n     <meta name=\"robots\" content=\"noindex\">\n     ```\n\n### Additional Steps:\n\n1. **Remove Sitemap**:\n   - If you have submitted a sitemap to Google Search Console, consider removing it to prevent Google from crawling and indexing your pages.\n\n2. **Monitor**:\n   - Regularly check Google Search Console to ensure that your removal requests are processed and that your pages are no longer indexed.\n\n### Important Note:\nDeindexing pages from Google can take some time to fully process. Make sure to check periodically and follow up if necessary.\n\nBy using these methods, you can effectively tell Google to deindex all pages of your site.",
